abstract: Jim Dwyer About New York column profiles Catherine Nolan, one of three candidates, along with Joseph D Morelle and Carl E Heastie, competing to replace disgraced Assembly Speaker Sheldon Silver.
lead_paragraph: As the competition to succeed the disgraced Sheldon Silver narrowed, Catherine Nolan, an assemblywoman for 30 years, said she had no intention of dropping out.
snippet: As the competition to succeed the disgraced Sheldon Silver narrowed, Catherine Nolan, an assemblywoman for 30 years, said she had no intention of dropping out.

headline.main: Race for Assembly Speaker Is a Fight Until the End
headline.print_headline: A Race That’s a Fight Until the End
